---
description: Pragmatic Skills Pack entry rule for repository work
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

For coding, debugging, planning, review, verification, and repository work, use the Pragmatic Skills Pack entry workflow. Prefer a project-local `skills/using-pragmatic-skills/SKILL.md` only when it exists; otherwise use the host-installed or global PSP runtime skills. Choose one primary mode and load supporting skills only when their phase trigger applies. Never invent command output, test results, review findings, or approvals. If the PSP runtime is unavailable, report that structured tracing is not enabled.
